<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-26T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-26T06:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 294/148: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-26T11:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">March 26,
                                        1923—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 26—9:22
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>147. W–12. How low a rate of interest would you accept if you approve in
                            principle of the plan for limiting loss by having the deficits carry
                            interest to establish the basis of 12 annual installments? <pb facs="0273" n="149" xml:id="pg_149"/> It is my suggestion that 4%
                            would not appear to be too low and that we might even make it somewhat
                            less. Wadsworth.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Herrick</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>